<%- include('partials/header') -%>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row mt-5">
      <div class="col-12">
        <ul class="row list-unstyled">

          <div class="absolute howTo">
            <h2>List of Items</h2>
            <span>Below are the list of items pick-ups! The format for the items are below</span>
            <table class = "table table-striped table-bordered">

              <tr>
                <td>Item Name</td>
                <td>The first line is the item name.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Item Description</td>
                <td>This will be the items description including how they stack when you have multiple items in the same run.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Stack Type</td>
                <td>Some items have different stack types and I feel it is important to note that. A linear stacktype is exactly how it sounds, if the item is +5%, then thats what it adds. A hyperbolic stack type slowely gets less effective the more you stack.</td>
              </tr>
            </table>

          </div>
          <div id="items" class="col-12">
          <% for(let i=0; i<items.length; i++) {%>
            <li>
              <br>
                  <h4><img src='<%=items[i].itemImage%>' loading="lazy"></h4>
                  <h4>-<%=items[i].itemName%></h4>
                  <h6>-<%=items[i].description%></h6>
                  <h6>-<%=items[i].stackType%></h6>
              </br>
            </li>

          <% } %>
          </ul>
      </div>
      <button onclick="topFunction()" id="myBtn" title="Go to top">Top</button>


          

      </div>  
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</div>
<%- include('partials/footer') -%>